                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p30g3hj48/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>immediately, &amp; you will notice several on my a/c who<lb/> have\n                                        paid in advance. You will also be kind enough<lb/> to send\n                                        me the a/c what <persName>Roggenburger &amp; Co</persName>\n                                        in <placeName>California</placeName><lb/> owes you.</p>\n                              <p>It was told me by several whose subscription<lb/> to the O. I have\n                                        sent the Last Time, that they have not<lb/> recd the O. You\n                                        will please therefore, to be exact in<lb/> making a plain\n                                        Direction; as our Post office arrangement<lb/> is none of\n                                        the Best.</p>\n                              <p>Business in general has been very good with us for<lb/> the last\n                                        10-12 Mos. &amp; Goods in almost all Branches<lb/> have paid\n                                        well to import; some articles always<lb/> pay very well in\n                                                  <placeName>California</placeName>; as for\n                                        Instance<lb/> Flour is worth from $40 to $45—pr.\n                                        Barrell,<lb/> which cost at Home no more than $4.50 pr\n                                        Barrel.<lb/> I could give you more Information about\n                                        Business<lb/> but I am aware, it is of no Interest to\n                                        you—<lb/> as you are no Doubt aware, money making &amp;<lb/>\n                                        speculating is all the go—&amp; one's attentions is\n                                        almost<lb/> entirely directed to that.</p>\n                              <p><persName>Mr. &amp; Mrs. Roggenburger</persName> desire their kind\n                                        Regards<lb/> to you; they have arrived <sic>save</sic>;\n                                        &amp; live very hand<lb/>-somely &amp; very convenient,\n                                        &amp; Enjoy themselves; they live<lb/> “<add>כשר</add>”\n                                        &amp; I am boarding with them, which gives me the\n                                        op-<lb/>-portunity of reminding myself, that I am a\n                                        “Secr”<lb/> Hoping, you will soon write to me a large letter\n                                        &amp;c, &amp; that this<lb/> may find you in good Health</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(9)\">I Remain your true friend</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(9)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">Cauffman H Meyer</persName>\n                              </p>\n                    </body>\n          </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p30g3hj48/canvas/p2"
                }
